00:05:56.059 --> 00:05:59.069
both from a strategic and a practical point of view.

00:05:59.909 --> 00:06:03.609
Not only did he learn how to command an army, but he

00:06:03.609 --> 00:06:06.279
would have learned how to fight from an early age.

00:06:07.649 --> 00:06:12.019
He was also, by all accounts, a talented and special boy.

00:06:13.229 --> 00:06:18.669
In one famous account, when Alexander was only 10 years old, a horse trader

00:06:18.869 --> 00:06:23.329
had brought a large black horse that he intended to sell to King Phillip.

00:06:23.939 --> 00:06:27.969
The horse was magnificent, but it was unrideable.

00:06:28.849 --> 00:06:33.119
Whenever anyone tried to approach, it would kick up its legs in the air, it

00:06:33.119 --> 00:06:39.109
seemed truly wild, too proud to be tamed by even the most capable of trainers.

00:06:40.309 --> 00:06:45.449
