00:18:55.142 --> 00:18:59.762
His lung had been punctured by an arrow, he had a serious neck and head

00:18:59.782 --> 00:19:05.042
injury after being hit by a stone fired from a crossbow, remember, he was

00:19:05.042 --> 00:19:10.702
fighting on the frontlines in serious battles almost non-stop for 13 years.

00:19:11.792 --> 00:19:17.642
What’s more, he was a big drinker, most probably an alcoholic by modern standards.

00:19:18.832 --> 00:19:21.962
In many ways, he was very lucky to have survived this

00:19:21.962 --> 00:19:26.682
long, and despite his young age, his body just gave up.

00:19:27.852 --> 00:19:31.092
But what certainly did survive is his legacy.

00:19:32.152 --> 00:19:37.862
One of his wives was pregnant when he died, but he left no surviving living heirs.

00:19:38.902 --> 00:19:45.872
And according to one popular legend, as he lay dying he was asked to whom he would leave his empire.

00:19:46.732 --> 00:19:50.892
He responded “to the strongest”, implying that he expected

00:19:50.892 --> 00:19:54.322
some kind of power struggle to ensue after his death.

00:19:55.602 --> 00:19:57.132
And, he was right.

00:19:58.202 --> 00:20:02.622
After his death his kingdoms were fought over and divided by his generals,

00:20:02.722 --> 00:20:07.492
but none would come anywhere near achieving the success that Alexander had.

00:20:08.542 --> 00:20:14.032
He had spread Greek culture and the Greek language across Asia, and for a short

00:20:14.052 --> 00:20:20.072
while, united tens of millions of people from Athens to Samarkand under one ruler.

